Here's a simple web game called "Adi's Room" where you click on rats to kill them within 30 seconds. The game features a menu and uses HTML, CSS, and JavaScript all in a single file. You can copy and paste the code below into an HTML file and open it in your web browser to play.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Adi's Room</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        #menu {
            margin: 20px;
        }
        #gameArea {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            height: 400px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            background-color: #fff;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
        .rat {
            position: absolute;
            width: 50px;
            height: 50px;
            background-image: url('https://img.icons8.com/ios-filled/50/000000/rat.png');
            background-size: cover;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        #timer {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        #score {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div id="menu">
        <h1>Adi's Room</h1>
        <button onclick="startGame()">Start Game</button>
        <div id="timer"></div>
        <div id="score"></div>
    </div>
    <div id="gameArea"></div>

    <script>
        let score = 0;
        let timer;
        let timeLeft = 30;

        function startGame() {
            score = 0;
            timeLeft = 30;
            document.getElementById('score').innerText = `Score: ${score}`;
            document.getElementById('timer').innerText = `Time Left: ${timeLeft}`;
            document.getElementById('gameArea').innerHTML = '';
            spawnRats();
            timer = setInterval(updateTimer, 1000);
        }

        function spawnRats() {
            const gameArea = document.getElementById('gameArea');
            const rat = document.createElement('div');
            rat.className = 'rat';
            rat.style.top = Math.random() * (gameArea.clientHeight - 50) + 'px';
            rat.style.left = Math.random() * (gameArea.clientWidth - 50) + 'px';
            rat.onclick = function() {
                score++;
                document.getElementById('score').innerText = `Score: ${score}`;
                gameArea.removeChild(rat);
                spawnRats();
            };
            gameArea.appendChild(rat);
            setTimeout(() => {
                if (gameArea.contains(rat)) {
                    gameArea.removeChild(rat);
                }
            }, 2000);
        }

        function updateTimer() {
            timeLeft--;
            document.getElementById('timer').innerText = `Time Left: ${timeLeft}`;
            if (timeLeft <= 0) {
                clearInterval(timer);
                alert(`Game Over! Your score is: ${score}`);
                document.getElementById('gameArea').innerHTML = '';
            }
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions to Play:
1. Copy the code above and paste it into a new file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `adis_room.html`).
2. Open the file in a web browser.
3. Click the "Start Game" button to begin.
4. Click on the rats that appear on the screen to score points.
5. You have 30 seconds to score as many points as possible. Good luck!
